      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "\n\n\nBOISE, May 29.-The police are\nworking hard to connect c. H. Dun\ncan, the socialist leader of the In\ndustrial Workers, with an alleged\nplot to kill Orchard before he takes\nthe stand. The mayor and chief\nare wiring every city in the west to\nget trace of his movements. He is\nlocked up and none is allowed to\nsee him.\n\n\nAuthorities mysteriously declare\na big sensation is impending. Dun\ncan had an automatic revolver,\nrazor-edged dirk, brass knuckles,\nETC., when arrested. The defense\nrepudiates him in the strongest\nterms. The mayor has ordered a\nsuspicion warrant filed and he will\nbe held indefinitely.\n\n\nIn another column The Press to-\nday gives Duncan's local career as\nan agitator. In this city he has\npassed as a radical but harmless\ncrank."
    }
  ]
